texts: Huh? This looks legit, doesn't it? It is, right?
As Wind found the airband recording, I opened 4chan.
I quickly shared it with everyone.
There's more to analyze. Someone found a URL.
WHOA! So it wasn't over with JA1037E?!
Could be. But it could just as well be real.
I'm bettin' it all on this, so help me out!
I can't say no to you when you're this serious! What about you two?
Yeah. I mean, there's no point half-assing it.
Under that assumption, I ran a tool on the image, but it didn't find any hidden data.
Cicada had already used steganography on his first Hihack post, so I didn't think he'd do it again.
Did that mean that the pic itself was the hint?
But finding the place it displayed was a real challenge. We needed more leads...
Shit! I don't get it at all!
In 20 minutes, we'd barely made any progress. We didn't know the place in the picture and hadn't found any other hints.
4chan kept talking about some "Swallow" place, but it didn't look like they'd completed the quest, either.
Hmm...I tried all the analysis methods people have used in the past, but I got nothing.
I'll start again and see if we missed anything.
No, wait. I think I got it.
I was wondering why this pic had these weird dimensions.
I thought they were coordinates, but they didn't lead to an actual place. When I switched up the numbers a bit, though...
The name of the place sounds Japanese...
I checked Ggoole Maps and the area looks like the place in the picture.
WOOO! YUMIKAWA! THAT WAS AWESOME! YOU'RE A WIZ!
I couldn't see anything weird on Ggoole Maps, so...
We probably gotta go to the place itself.
And just like that, I knew what to do!
Pollon, I'm coming with you. You might need help.
I set the coordinates to the place and we sped over there on my graper.
Flight 302 would go down in 15 minutes. Even if I hacked every traffic light, it was gonna be a close shave.
I parked my graper near the place in the coordinates.
I looked around and saw a scene exactly like the pic.
Pollon, the plane's about to come down.
Momo pointed at a nearby poster that had the cicada symbol and a QR code on it.
I read it using my BMI.
Congratulations. You are the first hacker to have arrived at the answer.
AHAHAHA! As if, you fucking dumbass!
I was just having some fun trolling idiots like you!
Now come on, let's watch 302 crash!
It was disinfo. Someone was fuckin' with us, for their own sick entertainment...
Just as the hackers predicted, Flight 302 ran out of fuel.
And so, Flight 302, with more than 200 passengers onboard, fell from the sky and crashed in Odaiba.
